  <text>
      <body>
        
     
      <div xml:id="OntheThreshold"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="FreeVerse"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="sad"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="death"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
              <l>O God, my dream! I dreamed that you were dead;</l>
          <l>Your mother hung above the couch and wept</l> 
          <l>Whereon you lay all white, and garlanded</l>
          <l>With blooms of waxen whiteness. I had crept</l>
          <l>Up to your chamber-door, which stood ajar,</l>
          <l>And in the doorway watched you from afar,</l>
          <l>Nor dared advance to kiss your lips and brow.</l>
          <l>I had no part nor lot in you, as now;,</l>
          <l>Death had not broken between us the old bar;</l>
          <l>Nor torn from out my heart the old, cold sense</l>
          <l>Of your misprision and my impotence.</l>
          
                 
